FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://127.0.0.1:5000

# Book Management API

A simple API to manage a collection of books, for SOA courses demo.

## Group Books

### Books Collection [/api/books]

#### Get all books [GET]
Get all books.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Book])

#### Add a new book [POST]
Add a new book.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (NewBook)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    Book created successfully.
    + Attributes (Book)

+ Response 400 (text/plain)
    Missing title or author.

### Single Book [/api/books/{book_id}]

+ Parameters
    + book_id: 1 (number, required) - ID of the book to retrieve, update, or delete.

#### Get a book by its ID [GET]
Get a book by its ID.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    The requested book.
    + Attributes (Book)

+ Response 404 (text/plain)
    Book not found.

#### Update an existing book [PUT]
Update an existing book.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (NewBook)

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    Book updated successfully.
    + Attributes (Book)

+ Response 400 (text/plain)
    Missing title or author.

+ Response 404 (text/plain)
    Book not found.

#### Delete a book [DELETE]
Delete a book.

+ Response 204
    Book deleted successfully.

+ Response 404 (text/plain)
    Book not found.

# Data Structures

## Book (object)
+ id: 1 (number, required) - The unique identifier of the book.
+ title: `Clean Code` (string, required) - The title of the book.
+ author: `Robert C. Martin` (string, required) - The author of the book.

## NewBook (object)
+ title: `Clean Code` (string, required) - The title of the book.
+ author: `Robert C. Martin` (string, required) - The author of the book.